Barí: Kamashkorou nondyiruku. It is commonly found in primary evergreen rainforest in the Bachichida and Baracai valley and on the Serrania de Abusanqui and Sierra de Perijá. The soil is normally sandy dark brown, quite humid and rich in humus. Tropical environment with an annual average of 27 C and 3500mm of rain with high humidity and a dry season from December 15 till March 15(with rain at least once a week).
